#. Tag: title
#: introduction.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:3
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&symboleditor; is used to create cross stitch symbols for the &kxstitch; "
"application. Originally &kxstitch; relied on standard character fonts to "
"supply these symbols, but differences in user languages and the quality of "
"the fonts available along with the alignment of the characters and the "
"limited number available has driven the need to create a dedicated symbol "
"set."
msgstr ""
"&symboleditor; se uporablja za ustvarjanje simbolov križnega šiva za "
"aplikacijo &kxstitch;. Prvotno se je &kxstitch; pri zagotavljanju teh "
"simbolov zanašala na standardne pisave znakov, vendar so razlike v "
"uporabniških jezikih in kakovosti pisav, ki so na voljo, skupaj s poravnavo "
"znakov in omejenim številom razpoložljivih, povzročile potrebo po "
"ustvarjanju namenskega nabora simbolov."

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:9
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The symbol set will be stored in a file and several files can be created "
"depending on the users needs, for example having a Halloween symbol set for "
"Halloween themed patterns."
msgstr ""
"Nabor simbolov bo shranjen v datoteki in glede na potrebe uporabnikov je "
"mogoče ustvariti več datotek, na primer imeti nabor simbolov za noč čarovnic "
"za vzorce na temo noči čarovnic."

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:13
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each of the files will contain a series of symbols which will be displayed "
"in the symbol library tab. Editing of existing symbols can be done by "
"clicking the entry in the library which will populate the editor with this "
"symbol. Alternatively new symbols can be created and added to the library."
msgstr ""
"Vsaka od datotek bo vsebovala vrsto simbolov, ki bodo prikazani na zavihku "
"knjižnice simbolov. Urejanje obstoječih simbolov lahko izvedete s klikom na "
"vnos v knjižnici, ki bo zapolnila urejevalnik s tem simbolom. Lahko pa "
"ustvarite nove simbole in jih dodate v knjižnico."

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:19
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please report any problems or feature requests to the &symboleditor; KDE "
"mailing list symboleditor@kde.org, you can subscribe <ulink url=\"http://"
"mail.kde.org/mailman/listinfo/symboleditor\">here</ulink> or the KDE bug "
"tracking system at <ulink url=\"http://bugs.kde.org/\">http://bugs.kde.org/</"
"ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Prosimo, da sporočite morebitne težave ali zahteve po funkcijah "
"&symboleditor; Dopisni seznam KDE symboleditor@kde.org, naročite se lahko "
"<ulink url=\"http://mail.kde.org/mailman/listinfo/symboleditor\">tukaj</"
"ulink> ali na sistem za sledenje hroščem KDE na <ulink url= \"http://bugs."
"kde.org/\">http://bugs.kde.org/</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The SymbolEditor home page is at <ulink url=\"http://userbase.kde.org/"
"SymbolEditor\">http://userbase.kde.org/SymbolEditor</ulink>"
msgstr ""
"Domača stran urejevalnika simbolov je na <ulink url=\"http://userbase.kde."
"org/SymbolEditor\">http://userbase.kde.org/SymbolEditor</ulink>"
